RE: How can the universe be uncaused? (22-08-2012 02:49 PM)Red Celt Wrote: (22-08-2012 02:39 PM)TrueReason Wrote: I believe that the universe must be caused by something that is not part of the physical universe because the universe (the result) cannot be its own cause. It's logically impossible.
We've already had this discussion in your introductory thread.
"God must be caused by something that is not part of God because God (the result) cannot be its own cause. It's logically impossible."
There you go. Disappear in a puff of your own logical smoke as you try and apply different criteria to the universe as you apply to your god.
I don't believe that there was a god that caused the physical universe, but it's not enough to claim it's logically impossible. That's the whole definition of the power of the monotheistic god...It defies logic. It is not bound by the laws of nature, if that's how it decides to act. We have to have a better refutation than just, "God is logically impossible."
You'll have to do better to make him disappear in a puff of smoke.
"All that is necessary for the triumph of Calvinism is that good Atheists do nothing." ~Eric Oh My
